# @pinta-ai/core is a PRIVATE GitHub Packages dependency. Its GitHub Packages
# URL is pinned in package-lock.json (no @pinta-ai scope redirect here, so this
# adapter's own @pinta-ai/* name still resolves to npmjs for publish/view).
# This line provides GitHub Packages auth in CI; core is bundled into dist/ at build.
#
# No registry.npmjs.org auth line: publishing uses npm OIDC trusted publishing
# (permissions.id-token: write + setup-node registry-url), which is how 0.1.0
# through 0.3.1 shipped. An _authToken line here expands to an empty string
# when no such secret exists and makes `npm publish` fail ENEEDAUTH instead of
# using OIDC.
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN}
